name: Orangutan
description: The orangutans (pongo) are a genus of primates in the family Hominidae. They differ from the other apes by their reddish-brown coat and by their body structure more adapted to a tree-dwelling way of life. They live on the Southeast Asian islands of Sumatra and Borneo; the populations of both islands are now kept as three separate species: Borneo-orangutan (Pongo pygmaeus), Sumatra-orangutan (Pongo abelii) and Tapanuli-orangutan (Pongo tapanuliensis).
